// Cortex-M3 + 64 KB SRAM / 512 KB flash (STM32F103RE-class), plus a RAM-mapped
// GPIOC register window for the thin-seam GPIO driver content-gate. The gate
// asserts the exact register values the DRIVER writes (CRH config nibble, BSRR
// set/reset) — its verified logic — so a plain memory region at the GPIOC base is
// the correct, deterministic model (no dependence on Renode's F1 GPIO peripheral
// electrical behaviour). USART1 is the real STM32 UART model, the report channel.
cpu: CPU.CortexM @ sysbus
    cpuType: "cortex-m3"
    nvic: nvic
nvic: IRQControllers.NVIC @ sysbus 0xE000E000
    -> cpu@0
flash: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x0
    size: 0x80000
sram: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x20000000
    size: 0x10000
// GPIOC register window (0x40011000) as plain memory — the driver's RMW of CRH and
// its BSRR writes store and read back deterministically; the gate checks those bytes.
gpioc: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x40011000
    size: 0x400
// USART1 — real STM32 USART model, the gate's report channel to the robot tester.
usart1: UART.STM32_UART @ sysbus <0x40013800, +0x100>
    -> nvic@37
